10 "Art. 316. Factors in fixing amount of bail
11 The amount of bail shall be fixed in an amount that will ensure the presence
12 of the defendant, as required, and the safety of any other person and the community,
13 having regard to:
14 (1) The seriousness of the offense charged, including but not limited to
15 whether the offense is a crime of violence, sex offense, or involves a controlled
16 dangerous substance.
17 * * *
18 (9) Whether a firearm or other dangerous weapon was possessed or used
19 during the commission of the offense.
20 (10) Whether available resources exist within the jurisdiction to impose
21 enforceable conditions that would help ensure the defendant's appearance and
22 protect the community.
23 (11) The likelihood that the defendant, if released on bail, will continue
24 to commit crimes resulting in harm to any person or the property of another.
25 (9)(12) Any other circumstances affecting the probability of defendant's
26 appearance.
27 (10)(13) The type or form of bail."
