30 "Art. 318. Juvenile records in fixing bail
31 A. For the purpose of fixing bail, a court may make a written request of any
32 juvenile court for an abstract containing only the pending or adjudicated delinquent
33 acts of a defendant currently before the requesting court. The request shall be
34 promptly complied with; however, juvenile court shall promptly comply with the
35 request; however, not more than forty-eight hours, exclusive of Saturdays, Sundays,
36 and legal holidays, shall lapse before the requested information is deposited in the
37 mail, by means of an email address provided in the written request addressed to
38 the requesting court.
39 B. The requesting court shall not copy, duplicate, or otherwise reproduce
40 such juvenile records, and these shall be deposited in the mail and addressed to the
41 issuing juvenile court within seventy-two hours, exclusive of Saturdays, Sundays,
42 and legal holidays, after bail is determined issue a protective order concerning the
43 use of the juvenile abstract for the purposes of protecting the confidentiality of
44 the abstract from any individual who is not involved in the relevant proceedings
45 that concern the defendant who is currently before the requesting court."
